description: Number of partitions of n into parts of 6 kinds.
comments: a(n) is Euler transform of A010722. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
links: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
Index entries for expansions of Product_{k >= 1} (1-x^k)^m
formula: G.f.: Product_{m>=1} 1/(1-x^m)^6.a(n) ~ exp(2 * Pi * sqrt(n)) / (16 * n^(9/4)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 28 2015
maple: with(numtheory): a:=proc(n) option remember; `if`(n=0, 1, add(add(d*6, d=divisors(j)) *a(n-j), j=1..n)/n) end: seq(a(n), n=0..40); # _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
crossrefs: Cf. 6th column of A144064. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
